.TH "rpc_uaddr2sockaddr" 9 "rpc_uaddr2sockaddr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpc_uaddr2sockaddr \- convert a universal address to a socket address.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "size_t" rpc_uaddr2sockaddr
.BI "(struct net *net "  ","
.BI "const char *uaddr "  ","
.BI "const size_t uaddr_len "  ","
.BI "struct sockaddr *sap "  ","
.BI "const size_t salen "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "net" 12
applicable network namespace
.IP "uaddr" 12
C string containing universal address to convert
.IP "uaddr_len" 12
length of universal address string
.IP "sap" 12
buffer into which to plant socket address
.IP "salen" 12
size of buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fIuaddr\fP does not have to be '\0'-terminated, but \fBkstrtou8\fP and
\fBrpc_pton\fP require proper string termination to be successful.

Returns the size of the socket address if successful; otherwise
zero is returned.
